The Federal Reserve, the European Central Bank and the central banks of Great Britain, Switzerland and Canada have decided to fight the crisis in the financial markets together.
This will bring over 100 billion dollars to the currency markets through auctions.
At these auctions, banks auction off interest rates at which they are willing to lend money to each other.
