"The European model of Melvin Benn is a rural festival, whereas ours is more of an urban green space", says Charlie Jones.
"The aim is to merge these two concepts in some way, to give the impression of a rural festival in the European way and an urban festival in the American way".
Vineland is about halfway between Philadelphia and Atlantic City.
"The Vineland community, including the mayor, is happy to take on the burden of this event", says Charlie Jones.
The latter refuses to disclose the terms of the agreement, but confirms "that they are sufficiently interesting to invest in such an event and to include a festival that will hopefully have a long life".
