What insurance plan is best for me?
Car insurance covering possible damage caused by the driver is a high cost, the amount of which depends on various factors, including age, gender, date of issue of the driving licence, marital status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
Owning a car is just the beginning.
It is even more difficult to find the right car insurance than the right car model.
First of all, you have to understand what we're dealing with here.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and an insured person.
This agreement is made in writing by means of an insurance contract, which stipulates that the company will receive the agreed insurance premium and is obliged to provide the corresponding amount of compensation in the event of damage.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance policy which is composed of several factors, including age, sex, date of issue of the driving licence, family status, type of vehicle to be insured or use.
Insurance companies set their prices according to the statistics, so that higher premiums are due if there is a higher risk of accidents.
This is why both over 25s and women have to pay less, as statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate due to their caution.
The same applies to married persons, who, according to statistics and thus also according to the belief of the undertakings, are less likely to have accidents than single persons.
The benefit attributed to the vehicle affects the frequency of driving and thus the likelihood of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
The insurance companies must take into account a number of factors when setting the premium.
This is why the driver must also study the situation thoroughly in order to choose the car insurance policy that best meets his personal needs.
We now list the main points to consider when choosing an insurance policy in order to make a choice based not only on performance but also on price.
The choice of a cheap insurance policy for those under 25 is hampered by a number of obstacles, such as lack of experience and a 'young' driving licence.
Even if the best way to obtain the best insurance coverage is to take out a full-scale insurance policy, there are cheaper alternatives.
The prudent driver can choose a self-insured full-cask insurance, so that the benefits of a full-cask insurance are covered but offered at a low price.
This type of contract involves the customer having to pay a part of the amount of the damage itself.
"The amount is determined before the contract is concluded and depends on the level of the insurance premium, which is higher the lower the amount to be paid", explains Luis Noguera, Spain's chief representative at First Europa, an online insurance brokerage.
Another option is extended insurance, which insures the customer against external accident damage but not against damage to the car itself.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire, and vehicle loss.
Here's a word of advice.
If you are under 25, it is up to you to reduce insurance costs, thus increasing your credit by trying to drive safely and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction in the basic rate of the insurance company concerned.
On the contrary, a penalty payment involves an increase in the tariff.
The amount of credits and fines depends on the company and its income.
If the company has a good year, it can afford to increase the bonus payments", explains Noguera.
Once the 25-year mark is passed, it is easier for drivers to conclude a contract, because the accident rate decreases as driving practice increases.
The most sensible option is to opt for a self-insurance scheme.
"Typically, young people cannot benefit from their previous experience, either in the event of an accident or at the time of driving", explains the Spanish head of the European company, adding that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of training after the "beginner's fear" has been put down.
However, it is more advisable for a married customer who does not have children to take out a full-scale insurance policy, of course only if the financial situation of the person concerned allows it.
The insurance companies consider couples with children to be the customers with the lowest accident rate and their contributions are also low accordingly.
In this case, full-scale insurance with self-insurance (around 300 euros) would be the best option.In the case of a high credit, extended insurance, which only starts in the third year of the vehicle, is recommended.
"They drive more relaxed overall and have greater purchasing power, which allows them to make higher contributions", notes Luis Noguera.
For pensioners, it is possible to take out a full-scale insurance with self-insurance (around EUR 150) or an extended insurance scheme, which is only used if the credit is sufficiently high.
Finally, it must be said that car insurance is a very important thing, not only because it protects the driver from possible accidental damage, but also because it carries high costs that require a thorough selection that is appropriate to our personal situation.
